reviews.text:
Still one of the best omakase stores in Hong Kong. Professional service, splendid taste of the freshly caught fish and perfect view of the Victoria Harbour. 

Absolutely a go to place for special occasions.

We ordered the omakase and it is good value for money. The sushi is fresh with generous portion. You can enjoy the harbour view too. 

That said I do not quite enjoy the whole experience (personal only). I do not like an uncle (looks like either the owner or a senior) popping in and out from the kitchen to the sushi counter where we were enjoying the Omakase. If you want to be out there, please wear a proper crisp white Chef attire, but not an old discolour one that looks like an underwear. No star is deducted for this point since this is just a personal view. Nothing wrong with their food. 

The sushi Chef is professional. Overall service is ok. If you want to enjoy the food with reasonable price, this is a place to be.

Went here for lunch. I had a $288 10 piece omakase sushi set. The fishes taste ok but not as good and fresh as other shops I had before. My husband has a winter special set which cost $298 but not as value as my sushi set and the portion is relatively less. I don't think I will come back again.

Very fresh and great Japanese sashimi and sushi. The omakase menu has 8 sashimi and 6 sushi, all with superb quality. The grilled fish is also very special and fatty, even for a person who doesn't like grilled fish that much. Overall very good quality Japanese that's a bit pricy.

Sushi lunch set is cheap. However, ingredients lacks flavor and freshness - most of the fish and shellfish don't have much taste. You can feel it is not very fresh. Sweet Ebi and Ark Shell were the best of the meal. At $208 it is still acceptable as you can get far worse for the same price at chain stores like Sen Ryo and Itacho. But don't expect top notch food at lunch. Maybe evening would be better?

reviews.text: Super delicious and fresh fish and oysters.  plus a super friendly Japanese chef!  Highly recommended!

Very delicious and authentic omakase. The Japanese sushi master is nice, talented and good at interacting with customers in four languages - Japanese, English, Mandarin and Cantonese. The sea urchin rice cup is unbeatable so are the Hokkaido scallops. Overall, it's a very good omakase dinner which tailor-made the best seasonal ingredients to make the most palatable dinner that stimulates my taste buds. Will definitely pay more visits in future.

Worst experience of omakase ever. I have tried at least 20 omakase restaurants in Hong Kong and this one is definitely the worst. Echo with first comment: low quality fish (not fresh at all!!), hot sushi rice (huh??????), strange environment etc. The table arrangement was weird too, as I have never seen a Japanese restaurant putting their chopsticks vertically. That’s for dead man in Japanese culture ok????

Should be my worst sushi experience ever , low quality ingredients, the sushi-rice tasted strange.  Also low skilled clumsy chef with poor preparation and presentation, while charged an expensive price, not to mention the crude décor...

Omakase 篇地開花，喜歡吃高質素食材的香港人有福了。今次我們去到亞士厘道這個食街，去品嚐高質素廚師發辦料理。

門口緊閉著，有點神祕感。開門後是一個日本廚師和一個日本女子做侍應。日本女子恭恭敬敬，而師傳則有點傲氣，想必對自家出品充滿信心。

先上的蒸蛋，慢慢滑入喉嚨，感受到其溫暖。蛋香細緻，配上香葉、本菇的，還是可以吃到雞蛋的滑。

而所有刺身、壽司，均十分出色。

最愛當然是我喜歡的左口魚群邊，經炙燒後，魚油都滿滿的融合在壽司飯中，香口無比。

整餐中，師傳不斷跟我們說到他拜師、做壽司的經驗、魚類的各種特性，增進了不少知識呢！

完全是日本口味日本氣氛的Omakase

師傅是日本人，對每樣食物有著日本人的堅持和介紹. 每一道食物於預備時會主動向客人介紹，例如介紹食物名、產地等. 又會主動問客人口味，Wasabi是否要，要多定少Wasabi.等等

有別於一般菜式，每道菜式味道很多層次，師傳會把不同食材同時使用，例如用藍諒包著蝦，再於外層加上少量蟹膏....大肥拖羅裏包著馬糞海膽...牡丹蝦外加上馬糞海膽....火炎大拖羅外加上黑魚子...每一種配搭都令食材味道更突出更鮮，而師傳亦堅持客人要一口食晒唔好咬開，因為咁樣先可以感受到成件食物既原味. 

其中一件為廣島蠔壽司，廣島蠔好明顯係新鮮即開蠔並唔係雪藏，師傳會先比濕紙巾你消毒雙手，然後要你申出手，將壽司放到你手中，並要你直接盡快放落口保留鮮味，一定要全隻食呀！真係神級既味道！

仲有一款馬糞海膽杯，整既時候已經見到佢真係一啲都唔孤寒，真係成杯都係好新鮮好鮮甜既海膽，仲真係北海道馬糞，種鮮甜真係好難忘.

平時食手卷，醬汁好多時會喺底漏出嚟，師傅特製既方法係唔會架，而且飯唔係太多，十分足料。

最後送上既係靜岡出產既密瓜，鮮甜多汁，令全餐晚飯或上完美既句號。

晚飯期間，太太不時都會幫忙加茶，亦會埋嚟閒談，旁邊有客人飯後一直坐喺度嘆酒，師傳仲會再整小食比佢送酒，服務真係非常好，而且食物質素真係絕對可以同日本本地既相比。
